item.title: How do i change the req lvl to cut down a certain tree?
item.dc:creator: @Itachi_Uchiha Itachi Uchiha
item.description:
@Itachi_Uchiha wrote:

Find your woodcutting cases in you client.java which should be

case 1276: case 1277: case 1278: case 1279: case 1280: case 1282: case 1283: case 1284: case 1285: case 1286: case 1289: case 1290: case 1291: case 1315: case 1316: case 1318: case 1319: case 1330: case 1331: case 1332: case 1365: case 1383: case 1384: case 2409: case 3033: case 3034: case 3035: case 3036: case 3881: case 3882: case 3883: case 5902: case 5903: case 5904:
under it should be some lines that look like this

Woodcutting.Woodcutting("", 1, 25, 1511, 1, objectID, objectX, objectY, 875, playerId); break;
The first 1 in that line is the level required to cut it

EX

Woodcutting.Woodcutting("oak", 15, 50, 1521, 1, objectID, objectX, objectY, 875, playerId); break;
Here is the oak tree line, if i wanted to change the level i would change it to 99 i would change it toâ€¦

Woodcutting.Woodcutting("oak", 99, 50, 1521, 1, objectID, objectX, objectY, 875, playerId); break;
